***Chesapeake Shores*** is a drama television series, based on the novel series [the same name](of)(Sherryl Woods#Chesapeake Shores) by [Woods](Sherryl)(Sherryl Woods), produced by Chesapeake Shores Productions Inc in association with Borderline Distribution. The series had a two-hour premiere on the [Channel](Hallmark)(Hallmark Channel) on August 14, 2016. [Metcalfe](Jesse)(Jesse Metcalfe), [Ory](Meghan)(Meghan Ory), [Niven](Barbara)(Barbara Niven), [J. Mailey](Laci)(Laci J. Mailey), [Ullerup](Emilie)(Emilie Ullerup), [Penny](Brendan)(Brendan Penny), [Francis](Andrew)(Andrew Francis), [Ladd](Diane)(Diane Ladd) and [Williams](Treat)(Treat Williams) star in the series. [Tinker](John)(John Tinker (TV producer)) was [showrunner](showrunner) and executive producer for the first two seasons. [Sutton](Phoef)(Phoef Sutton) became the showrunner and principal writer for season five.

In March 2021, it was announced that Metcalfe would be exiting the series. His character's storyline concluded early in the fifth season. Actor [Buckley](Robert)(Robert Buckley) joined the main cast in season five. The show's fifth season aired from August 15 to October 17, 2021. The series' sixth and final season premiered on August 14, 2022, with the series finale airing on October 16.
